</metadata>

<content>
    <para id="import-auto-id1163826627089">
      <emphasis effect="bold">Step by Step Model for Sampling Distribution and Confidence Intervals</emphasis>
    </para>
    <table id="import-auto-id1163826626862" summary="">
      <tgroup cols="2">
        <colspec colnum="1" colname="c1"/>
        <colspec colnum="2" colname="c2"/>
        <thead>
          <row>
            <entry><emphasis effect="bold">Plan:</emphasis> State what we need to know.</entry>
            <entry>Enter your plan here</entry>
          </row>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry><emphasis effect="bold">Model:</emphasis> Think about the assumptions and check the conditions. </entry>
            <entry> List your assumptions here and state how the assumptions have been met</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry>State the parameters and the sampling model.</entry>
            <entry>Provide the formulas you will use and then use the formulas to determine the parameters</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry><emphasis effect="bold">Plot:</emphasis>  Make a picture. Sketch the model and shade the area weâ€™re interested in.  </entry>
            <entry>Insert a graphic display of your model here. You can use the link at <link url="http://socr.ucla.edu/htmls/SOCR_Distributions.html"><emphasis effect="underline">http://socr.ucla.edu/htmls/SOCR_Distributions.html</emphasis></link> to create the model and then paste it here.</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry>
              <para id="import-auto-id1163826650460">
                <emphasis effect="bold">Mechanics</emphasis>
              </para>
            </entry>
            <entry>Provide the formulas you will use and then use the formulas to determine distribution score and the probability of that score.</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry><emphasis effect="bold">Conclusion:</emphasis> Interpret your result in the proper context, and relate it to the original question. </entry>
            <entry/>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </table>
